HEADWORD: Celebrant
<hw>Cel"e*brant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>celebrans</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>celebrare</ets>. See
<er>Celebrate</er>.]</ety> <def>One who performs a public religious
rite; -- applied particularly to an officiating priest in the Roman
Catholic Church, as distinguished from his assistants.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Celebrate</ent>⟦br⟧
